<item>
            <title>[LU-13703] fix lfs_migrate to work with PFL arguments</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13703</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Using the &lt;tt&gt;lfs_migrate&lt;/tt&gt; script with PFL arguments that contain &quot;&lt;tt&gt;&amp;#45;&amp;#45;stripe&amp;#45;count&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; or &quot;&lt;tt&gt;&amp;#45;&amp;#45;stripe&amp;#45;size&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; (which is very likely) will result in &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lfs_migrate&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; parsing the last incidence of those values as the global stripe count/size and not work properly if different values are specified for different components.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Instead, if a PFL layout is specified on the command-line (even if migrating a file &lt;b&gt;to&lt;/b&gt; a PFL layout) is not necessarily the most optimal solution, it should be handled properly.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
